# Source Code

This directory contains the core implementation of the **Real-Time Object Detection** system.

## Files

### `realtime_detection.py`
- Detects objects from a live webcam feed.
- Uses the YOLOv3 deep learning model with OpenCV.
- Displays detected objects with bounding boxes, class labels, confidence scores, and object counts.
- Provides an interactive Tkinter-based graphical user interface.

### `image_detection.py`
- Detects objects in static images.
- Loads an input image, performs inference using YOLOv3, and displays the detection results with labels and confidence scores.

## Technologies Used

- Python
- OpenCV
- YOLOv3
- NumPy
- Pillow
- Tkinter
- Matplotlib

## Purpose

The source code is organized separately to improve project structure, readability, and maintainability.
